Global setup:
 Set up git     -> Indicates which user made the change
1.  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
2.  git config --global user.email smitathaker@gmail.com
      
Next steps:
3.  mkdir HelloGit2
4.  cd HelloGit2
5.  git config color.ui true
6.  git init        -> Initialize git
7.  touch README
8.  git add README
9.  git commit -m 'first commit'
10.  git remote add origin git@github.com:smitathaker/HelloGit2.git  -> Done once per repository. It tells your local computer that github is holding all ur files
                                                                  -> declares git@github.com:smitathaker/HelloGit2.git as the origin
11.  git push -u origin master           -> push all changes of master branch to the origin server.     
      
Existing Git Repo?
4.  cd existing_git_repo
5.  git remote add origin git@github.com:smitathaker/HelloGit2.git
6.  git push -u origin master